[shake]INTERCOM: [shake]You've gone further than most.[/shake]
[shake]INTERCOM: [shake]That won't change where this ends.[/shake]
Conductor: There you are.
Conductor: You've been irregular since the platform.
Conductor: Too much movement. Too many routes. Passengers don't navigate. They ride.
Conductor: But you — you saw something on the train. Most of them never see anything.
Conductor: That's why I've been watching you.
You: You gave me the punch. On the train.
Conductor: I needed to see what you'd do with it.
Conductor: You passed that part.
You: What do you want from me?
Conductor: This position requires someone who can see the anomalies. Who notices when the system is showing through.
Conductor: I've been here long enough.
You: You want a replacement.
Conductor: I want someone who is ready for it.
Conductor: You're not. Not yet.
Conductor: But you collected quite a few.
Conductor: It won't matter. Not today.
Conductor: Irregular passengers get reassigned.
Conductor: Your new route is ready.
